snippet.textDisplay: Guys you can do better. Especially given the stated purpose of being practical knowledge . You’ve fallen into the trap that similar internet videos do. They compare bottom shelf with special order. I mean, I doubt that they have £700 chocolate at most grocery stores. What we need to know is it worth spending 2-3 times for the “better” product. Not if it’s worth taking out a loan before I go to the grocery store or not. Let’s be practical here. In fact, if you can’t find both items in the same store (preferably on the same shelf,) don’t include them.
